# Backend conventions

## Code style

- `declare(strict_types=1)` in every file.
- PHP CS Fixer `@Symfony` ruleset. No Yoda comparisons (`$x === null`, not `null === $x`).
- Final classes for controllers and services. Constructor property promotion with `private readonly`.
- PHPStan level 9 — all code must pass. Use `@phpstan-type` / `@phpstan-param` for generics.

## Controllers

- Namespace: `App\Controller\Api\Admin\` or `App\Controller\Api\Customer\`.
- Extend `AbstractController`. Route attributes on class and methods.
- Constructor DI with repositories/services. Return `$this->json()`. Use `ApiNormalizer`.
- Type-hint `Customer` or `User` as action parameter — resolved automatically.

## Entities

- Doctrine PHP 8 attributes. UUID string IDs (`GeneratedValue(strategy: 'NONE')`).
- Embeddable VOs in `Entity\Embeddable\`.

## Testing

- PHPUnit: `tests/Unit/` and `tests/Integration/`. Files named `*Test.php`, methods `test<Behavior>`.
- Integration tests use `WebTestCase::createClient()` + `ApiTestHelper`.
- Bootstrap recreates schema from scratch — no migration dependency.

## Commands

```bash
vendor/bin/php-cs-fixer fix --dry-run --diff   # style check
vendor/bin/phpstan analyse                       # static analysis (after cache:warmup)
php bin/phpunit                                  # tests
```
